tip.text: If you're a big fan of Japanese food, this is the place. Staff are quite attentive.
Visited their sister outlet in Scott's Square this June. The place's nicely decorated and a bit more spacious compared to the one in Mandarin Gallery. Their food made my day.
Having Wild Mocha Dolce at Wild Honey Scott's Square. Service is prompt and food's great.
One of my fav corners in town since I was in uni. Food is super duper. Scandi, Belgian & Apple Crumble are my all-time favourites.
Tasty food and friendly staff. Everything is just nice and worth the money.

The menu offers a great choice of dishes. Nicely decorated and brings cozy atmosphere to customers. Portion of noodles and some others can be a bit smaller than expected compared to the prices we pay.

This is a very hip and trendy cafe on River Valley Close area. I found the service good as well as the food. A great selection of food and drinks on offer with reasonable prices. Below's salmon ceasar

EXECEPTIONAL- One of the best in Tanjong Pagar. The team never fails to amaze me with their fantastic food and service. Let me not spoil it by giving all their secrets. You just have to visit b4 July.
Sichuan wonton never fails to make my day.
Not a worry at Teck Seng. Soybean milk, beancurd or a mix of soybean milk and grass jelly, they have it all; but for me soybean milk alone justifies the visit. [Quick Tip] Come early on the weekend.
Durian Mango Sago is my all time favorite.

formattedAddress: #01-11, Liang Seah Place (1 Liang Seah St)

venue.name: Ah Chew Desserts 阿秋甜品

tip.text: Been back to the bistro twice this week and healthy choice of tea wins. Btw, wifi password is chapter55.
If I'm not wrong it's a new restaurant in the neighborhood. Excellent aglio lio, and of course carbonara is nice too. Don't miss the tea options which have some organic teas. GREAT service so far.
Nothing special bout this place unfortunately; except the prices (2-4pax) are on par which come with a set of tofu, vegs, chicken, pork and soup. The pork chop is nice to some certain extent.

venue.name: Zheng Swee Kee Pte Ltd 正瑞记海南鸡饭

tip.text: The crispy duck (Rp 125,000) is indeed very good, tender, succulent and flavourful with a crackly-crisp skin. In a word, heavenly. Good view of rice paddle field. Staff is nice and friendly. A star.
GREAT live music. Got a chance to meet such a lovely duo tonight and enjoyed their songs a great deal. Prices are not so bad compared to other bars (taxes and service charge not included).
Want something local, this is the place. Food is on par and nice staff.
The band tonight was cool. Staff is friendly.
Not bad for a quick bite. Thoi the portion is a bit small but it could keep you going till late at night.
I said I'd come back and here I did. Like the service here. Had some Thai noodle and it was tasty. Worth a try.

Fresh fish here is quite good but a bit expensive (50,000rph) compared to its super small portion; however as its in the centre where lotsa tourists stay so its fair enough.But service is really good.
Wifi password: mAtAhAricAfe

Nice place, esp its good for couples : ) From the cafe you could enjoy the sunset view which is absolutely stunning. Friendly staff. They have FREE shuttle bus service. Do approach staff for more info
Had lunch today and must say, the food there is good. I had some Indonesian salad and it killed. Fantastic view. Staff seems nice and helpful; however, the prices are quite expensive. Taxes excluded.

formattedAddress: Italian Beachside Restaurant & Swimming Pool (Jl. Raya Senggigi, Batu Bolong)

tip.text: Wifi password.
Very centrally located and its only 5 mins away from the airport. The staff is super nice, helpful and friendly. Rooms are clean and spacious. What's more, the food in the restaurant is delicious.
Excellent service- Amazingly friendly staff and rooms are just amazing. Competitive room rates in town. What else could I ask for? Terima kasih, The Alit.
Super nice milkshakes and the latte wasnt bad, but what impressed me the most was the friendly service that P&C has offered. As for the prices, uhm, well they're not unexpensive.
Nice place for group catch-ups. Drinks are on par and the music is pretty cool thou. Don't miss the special deals for Mojito on Saturdays (9pm-midnight, if I'm not wrong).
Tea leaf salad (or Laphet Thoke) is a must try dish.

Nice spot to rest you legs after a long day biking around the town. The food is just so yummy with affordable prices. Not to mention the friendly and helpful staff. They speak English fluently as well
Appears to be a very nice spot in downtown Yangon. Friendly staff, tasty food, wide choices of menu and the prices are quite on par, esp if you're travelling and dont mind paying a little bit more.
Friendly service staff as mentioned in the prev tip. Weekdays would be the perfect time to sit down and enjoy a coffee or two in a private corner and watch people passing by.
Good service thou its part of self-service. Studio M should feel lucky to have good service staff thou two of them were only trainees. Give them a thumbs up.
Great service staff. I just stopped by The Book Cafe yesterday for a drink to cool down the heat in Singapore. Longan Frosty killed.
